{#-
  Popover — floating panel anchored to a trigger.

  JS-positioned (Floating UI v1.7 via the `popover` Stimulus controller) with
  viewport-aware collision detection (flip + shift). The kit's overlay
  foundation; downstream compounds (Combobox, DropdownMenu, ContextMenu,
  HoverCard, DatePicker, Select) all compose this.

  Popover is **non-modal** — the trigger keeps focus on open; the user Tabs
  into the content when they choose. For modal flows (focus trap, backdrop,
  blocks rest of page), use `Dialog` (Ring 2).

  Stimulus controller `popover`:
    - `toggle()` flips openValue; the value-changed callback dispatches
      show()/hide().
    - `open()` / `close()` — explicit methods (consumers wiring custom
      semantics).
    - `popover:open` / `popover:close` raw CustomEvents (bubbles + composed)
      with detail.placement (resolved after Floating UI's `flip`).
    - Esc dismiss via @window binding (closes any open popover when Esc is
      pressed anywhere).
    - Click-outside dismiss via document-capture-phase listener.

  Positioning is **physical** (px-based `left` / `top` set inline by Floating
  UI). The kit's ONE documented exception to "logical CSS everywhere" —
  Floating UI handles RTL internally via its platform layer. See
  `src/styles/components/popover.css` §positioning for the rationale.

  Parameters:
    htmlId       (string, optional)  — auto-generated; used to chain
                                       aria-controls + the content's id so
                                       the consumer's trigger can post
                                       aria-controls="{{ popoverHtmlId }}".
    placement    (string, optional)  — bottom (default) | top | start | end.
                                       'start' / 'end' are logical aliases
                                       converted to Floating UI's physical
                                       'left' / 'right' per document direction.
    offset       (int,    optional)  — gap from trigger in px (default 8).
    open         (bool,   optional)  — false (default). SSR-open popovers.
    className    (string, optional)  — extra utility classes on the wrapper.
    contentClassName (string, optional) — extra classes on the content panel.

  Blocks (one required each):
    trigger — the element that toggles the popover. The Twig stamps
              `data-popover-target="trigger"`, `aria-haspopup="dialog"`,
              `aria-expanded` (initial value), `aria-controls` automatically
              IF the block doesn't override them. The consumer block content
              is the trigger's own innards (label, icon, etc.). For richer
              semantic control (e.g. DropdownMenu wants `aria-haspopup="menu"`),
              the consumer overrides via attributes in the block.
    content — the floating panel's body. Consumer-provided HTML. The Twig
              wraps it in a `<div data-popover-target="content">` with
              positioning + animation styles applied.
-#}

{%- set htmlId            = htmlId            | default('cremona-popover-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set placement         = placement         | default('bottom') -%}
{%- set offset            = offset            | default(8) -%}
{%- set open              = open              | default(false) -%}
{%- set className         = className         | default('') -%}
{%- set contentClassName  = contentClassName  | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['cremona-popover'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set _contentClasses = ['cremona-popover__content'] -%}
{%- if contentClassName -%}{%- set _contentClasses = _contentClasses | merge([contentClassName]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set popoverHtmlId = htmlId -%}

<div
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-controller="popover"
  data-action="click->popover#toggle keydown.esc@window->popover#close"
  data-popover-placement-value="{{ placement }}"
  data-popover-offset-value="{{ offset }}"
  data-popover-open-value="{{ open ? 'true' : 'false' }}"
>
  {%- block trigger -%}{%- endblock -%}
  <div
    id="{{ popoverHtmlId }}"
    class="{{ _contentClasses | join(' ') }}"
    data-popover-target="content"
    data-state="{{ open ? 'open' : 'closed' }}"
    data-placement="{{ placement }}"
    {{ open ? '' : 'hidden' }}
  >
    {%- block content -%}{%- endblock -%}
  </div>
</div>
